    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Rhodiola Gummies</h2>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What does rhodiola rosea do?</summary><p>Rhodiola is an adaptogen that fights fatigue and enhances performance by modulating the HPA axis (cortisol) and inhibiting MAO (preserving dopamine, serotonin, norepinephrine). Clinically shown to improve cognitive function, reduce fatigue, enhance endurance, and support mood.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How much rhodiola should I take?</summary><p>200-600mg daily, standardized to 3% rosavins and 1% salidroside. For fatigue: 200-400mg. For burnout: 400-600mg. Take in the morning (energizing effects can disrupt sleep). Effects in 1-3 weeks, optimal at 4-8 weeks.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Is rhodiola better than ashwagandha?</summary><p>Different purposes. Rhodiola is energizing (dopamine, norepinephrine) — best for fatigue, focus, motivation. Ashwagandha is calming (GABA, cortisol) — best for anxiety, sleep, stress. Rhodiola for morning energy, ashwagandha for evening calm. Can combine both.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Does rhodiola help with depression?</summary><p>Clinical trial found rhodiola comparable to sertraline for mild depression with fewer side effects. Mechanism: MAO inhibition preserves serotonin/dopamine. Best when fatigue and low motivation accompany depression. Not a replacement for prescribed antidepressants in moderate-severe cases.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can I take rhodiola every day?</summary><p>Yes. Safe for daily use up to 12 weeks in clinical trials. Traditional use spans centuries. Some practitioners recommend cycling (5 on/2 off). Take mornings only. Start at 200mg, increase based on response. Minimum 4-8 weeks for full assessment.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What should I look for in rhodiola supplements?</summary><p>Standardization to 3% rosavins, 1% salidroside (SHR-5 ratio). Third-party identity verification (rhodiola adulteration is documented). 200-600mg dose per serving. Morning dosing recommended. Avoid products without standardization or botanical verification.</p></details>

